🔹 Step 1: Go to Your Project Folder
cd ~/vedic_horoscope_bot

🔹 Step 2: Activate Your Python Virtual Environment
source venv/bin/activate

🔹 Step 3: Start the Flask Backend API
This API runs on port 5001 and serves planetary calculations + Claude AI prediction:
python app.py
(Keep this terminal open — or run it in the background using nohup python app.py &)

🔹 Step 4: Open a New Terminal & Reactivate venv
cd ~/vedic_horoscope_bot
source venv/bin/activate

🔹 Step 5: Start the Streamlit Frontend
This will open the UI in your browser:

streamlit run horoscope_bot.py

🔹 Step 6: Open the App in Your Browser
Visit:
http://localhost:8501
Or if it's hosted on a remote server (e.g., EC2):

http://<your-ec2-public-ip>:8501
📝 Summary of Commands:

# Terminal 1
cd ~/vedic_horoscope_bot
source venv/bin/activate
python app.py

# Terminal 2 (new tab)
cd ~/vedic_horoscope_bot
source venv/bin/activate
streamlit run horoscope_bot.py
